(MULTIPLAYER GAMING SITE: 100 SMALL STEPS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This roadmap is designed for building your site from scratch with Node.js, Express,) Tj
T*
(WebSocket, MongoDB, EJS, and vanilla JavaScript. Follow the steps in order. Each step is) Tj
T*
(intentionally small so you can build with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 1: PROJECT SETUP) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Create the project folder and initialize it with `npm init -y`.) Tj
T*
(2. Rename the project in `package.json` to something clear like `multiplayer-gaming-site`.) Tj
T*
(3. Set `"main"` to `server.js` instead of `index.js`.) Tj
T*
(4. Create a `.gitignore` file for `node_modules`, `.env`, logs, and OS files.) Tj
T*
(5. Create the base folders: `config`, `src`, `routes`, `views`, `public`, `tests`, `docs`.) Tj
T*
(6. Install core dependencies: `express`, `mongoose`, `dotenv`, `cookie-parser`,) Tj
T*
(`express-session`, `bcryptjs`.) Tj
T*
(7. Install realtime and utility dependencies: `ws` or `socket.io`, `connect-mongo`,) Tj
T*
(`morgan`, `helmet`, `compression`.) Tj
T*
(8. Install development dependencies: `nodemon` and a test runner such as `jest`.) Tj
T*
(9. Add scripts in `package.json` for `dev`, `start`, and `test`.) Tj
T*
(10. Create `server.js` as the entry point that starts the HTTP server.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 2: APP FOUNDATION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. Create `app.js` to configure Express separately from the server startup.) Tj
T*
(12. In `app.js`, enable `express.urlencoded\(\)` and `express.json\(\)`.) Tj
T*
(13. Add `cookie-parser` middleware.) Tj
T*
(14. Add `helmet` middleware for basic security headers.) Tj
T*
(15. Add `compression` middleware for faster responses.) Tj
T*
(16. Add `morgan` for development request logging.) Tj
T*
(17. Set the view engine to `ejs`.) Tj
T*
(18. Point Express to the `views` folder.) Tj
T*
(19. Expose the `public` folder with `express.static\(\)`.) Tj
T*
(20. Export the configured app from `app.js`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 3: ENVIRONMENT AND DATABASE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(21. Create a `.env` file for local secrets and config.) Tj
T*
(22. Create `.env.example` with placeholder values for future setup.) Tj
T*
(23. Add `PORT`, `MONGO_URI`, `SESSION_SECRET`, and `NODE_ENV` to the env files.) Tj
T*
(24. Create `config/env.js` to read and validate environment variables.) Tj
T*
(25. Create `config/db.js` to connect to MongoDB using Mongoose.) Tj
T*
(26. Call the DB connection before starting the server.) Tj
T*
(27. Log a clear success message when MongoDB connects.) Tj
T*
(28. Log a clear error message and exit if DB connection fails.) Tj
T*
(29. Create `config/session.js` for shared session configuration.) Tj
T*
(30. Store sessions in MongoDB with `connect-mongo`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 4: FOLDER STRUCTURE AND CONVENTIONS) Tj
ET
endstream
