() Tj
T*
(31. Inside `src`, create `modules`, `middlewares`, `services`, `utils`, and `sockets`.) Tj
T*
(32. Inside `src/modules`, create folders for `auth`, `users`, `games`, `chat`, `friends`,) Tj
T*
(`leaderboard`, and `matchmaking`.) Tj
T*
(33. Decide a naming convention like `feature.controller.js`, `feature.service.js`,) Tj
T*
(`feature.routes.js`.) Tj
T*
(34. Keep all database models inside their feature folders.) Tj
T*
(35. Keep shared helpers in `src/utils`.) Tj
T*
(36. Keep shared middlewares in `src/middlewares`.) Tj
T*
(37. Keep WebSocket bootstrapping in `src/sockets/index.js`.) Tj
T*
(38. Create `routes/index.js` for mounting all HTTP routes in one place.) Tj
T*
(39. Keep browser-side JavaScript in `public/js`.) Tj
T*
(40. Keep all page templates in `views/pages` and reusable UI parts in `views/partials`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 5: BASIC PAGES AND LAYOUT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(41. Create a base layout file such as `views/layouts/main.ejs`.) Tj
T*
(42. Create shared partials: `navbar.ejs`, `footer.ejs`, and `flash.ejs` if needed.) Tj
T*
(43. Create a simple home page at `views/pages/home.ejs`.) Tj
T*
(44. Create login and register pages.) Tj
T*
(45. Create a lobby page where logged-in users will enter multiplayer mode.) Tj
T*
(46. Create a local game page for guests who want to play with a bot.) Tj
T*
(47. Create placeholder pages for friends, chat, leaderboard, and profile.) Tj
T*
(48. Add a common CSS file in `public/css/style.css`.) Tj
T*
(49. Add a common frontend file in `public/js/main.js`.) Tj
T*
(50. Confirm all pages render correctly through Express routes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 6: USER MODEL AND AUTHENTICATION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(51. Create `src/modules/users/user.model.js`.) Tj
T*
(52. Add fields like `username`, `email`, `passwordHash`, `avatar`, `rating`, and) Tj
T*
(`friendsCount`.) Tj
T*
(53. Add timestamps to the user schema.) Tj
T*
(54. Add unique indexes for `username` and `email`.) Tj
T*
(55. Create `src/modules/auth/auth.validation.js` to validate register and login input.) Tj
T*
(56. Create `auth.service.js` to handle password hashing and account lookup.) Tj
T*
(57. Use `bcryptjs` to hash passwords during registration.) Tj
T*
(58. Create `auth.controller.js` for register, login, and logout handlers.) Tj
T*
(59. Create `auth.routes.js` and mount it under `/auth`.) Tj
T*
(60. Use sessions so logged-in users stay authenticated between requests.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PHASE 7: AUTH MIDDLEWARES AND PROTECTED ROUTES) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(61. Create `auth.middleware.js` to allow only logged-in users.) Tj
T*
(62. Create `guest.middleware.js` for pages that should only be visible before login.) Tj
T*
(63. Save the logged-in user ID in the session after successful login.) Tj
T*
(64. Load the current user from the session on every request.) Tj
T*
(65. Expose the current user to all EJS templates through `res.locals`.) Tj
T*
(66. Protect the lobby, profile, friends, chat, and multiplayer routes.) Tj
ET
